text.tspan: Batch Queue
a) Select File/Open with manual edge selection
b) Using the file dialog select one or more
file with multi-select (shift-click or ctrl-click)
Remember that you can sort by file type or
by date to make selection more convenient
a) Manual ROI selection dialog opens
c) Note the number of queued files
This will update dynamically if
raw development takes a while
b) Draw or load ROIs as required
a) You may repeat step (1) above if you want to add more
files, useful when files are in separate directories
b) You may even use the Preferences dialog in between to
tweak raw development options, e.g., Bayer channel,
or pixel size
Preferences will apply to all subsequent files; these are
associated at the time a file is opened and will remain
set for that file as it is processed)
c) As you add more files, the 'Queued' files will
update as raw development proceeds
a) You may adjust or load ROIs as desired, clicking on
'Accept' to process only the displayed file
Remaining files in the queue will load and display
one-at-a-time as you click 'Accept' each time
b) Alternatively, you may click on 'Accept queued' to process
all remaining queued files using the current ROIs
This is intended for processing repeated shots of the exact
same edge, such as when focus bracketing, or stopping
down.
Do not use 'Accept queued' if any edge shifts more than 3-4
pixels relative to the ROI centreline in any queued image, in
the direction perpendicular to the edge
